The article discusses a background briefing by senior administration officials on an Iranian nuclear facility. The officials provide information on the history of the Iranian nuclear issue, particularly the construction of a secret underground enrichment facility known as the Natanz facility. They also reveal the existence of a second underground enrichment facility near the city of Qom, which is heavily protected and disguised. The officials explain that the facility is designed to produce a small amount of weapons-grade uranium without the international community knowing about it. The officials emphasize the importance of Iran taking concrete action to address the concerns of the international community, and they discuss the upcoming October 1st meeting where Iran will be pressed to cooperate with the investigation of the facility by the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA). The officials also mention the possibility of sanctions if diplomacy fails and the need for international consensus and cooperation in dealing with Iran's nuclear program.